texts.text: >Due to your efforts, the enemy ranks are starting to break.
This is our chance!
Here goes!
>Just as the demon in front of the device is defeated, Masaki rushes forward.
No you don't!
>But the Holy Maiden herself steps in to block Masaki...!
I don't want to kill you! Out of my way!
I will not!
Then I will make you...!
Filthy rebel...! Your Eminence, get back!
Masaki! Watch out!
Huh...?
*Howl*
*Hiss*
Oof... Aaaargh!
Masaki!
I... I'm not finished!
[sys user_name]!
Please... Get my men out of here now.
I will do what I came here to do. I will stop the Holy Maiden!
>You see that Masaki is holding what looks like a bomb in his hand...
Sneaky little... Get him!
Rip him apart if you have to, I want that man stopped!
As you wish, Your Eminence!
>Just when the Holy Maiden's men gang up on Masaki...
>The room turns white as a flash of light
>bursts through a window above accompanied by a loud thunderclap.
...Yuna.
Ma... Masaki...?
>The bomb in Masaki's hand drops to the ground
>as he murmurs a name unfamiliar to all...

No... Masaki...
Wait, why am I...
Hey [sys user_name], she just called him Masaki...!
>Upon hearing her own name, the Holy Maiden
>Yuna can feel a flood of memories coming back to her.
Look at her eyes Masaki, they're just like yours.
And our child's nose looks just like yours.
The nose? Why would I be happy that... Wait, it actually does make me happy she has my nose.
Our child is the sum of us.
There's no better feeling in the world than that.
Yes, you're right. I am so happy.
Nooo!! Why?! Why did this happen to her...?!
It's those monsters. The demons...
We have to run! But before that, we have to put our child to rest. With our own hands...
*Sob* Why...? Why does she have to die...?!
Without her, I have nothing to live for...
Don't say that!
If there's anything that can be done to save her, I'd do it in a heartbeat!

But she's beyond help...
And I can't stand it if I lose you too...
We couldn't protect our baby girl, but we have to protect ourselves.
We will endure. That is how we defy the world.
It is as I thought, this water...
You found something?
This water can erase memories...
Or rather it can overwrite them.
It puts a blank slate over your original memories for imprint.
It builds a new memory storage in your brain, cutting off access to the old one.
A new memory storage?
Well you're the leading expert on brain functions in Japan, so it must be true.
That title has no meaning anymore. Not in this world.
But with this water, we can...
So you've made up your mind?
Yes. With this, we can start a new life.
We can erase our memory of the past, leaving general knowledge and crucial memories untouched.
We'll be able to live free of the past because we won't remember what we've lost in the destruction.
Then we can build a strong society united under one leader.
And as a unified group, humanity can endure.
...We have to endure, for her sake.
Alright. I'll tell the city.
...But I'll ask you one more time, just in case.
Are you sure you really want to take on the role of the leader yourself?
The people of the city chose you, but what if something happened to you...?
I'm willing to take the risk. I will be...
I will become the worker of miracles. The Holy Maiden.
It's been done. That leaves just the two of us now.
Yes. Are you scared?
I might ask you the same thing.
*Chuckle*
Let's hope we'll still love each other even when we lose our memories.
I'm sure we will. The purpose of this is to bind people together.
So I have no doubt we'll be together again.
I... remember now.

Masaki... Masaki!
I'm sorry, I...
Just like Frankenstein's monster... A ragtag bunch of parts sown together...
Memories erased, overwritten... Ragtag recollections...
Hehe... So this is the ugly face of our true memories...
>Having said that, Masaki and Yuna both break down crying.
>You leave without a word...
Hey, [sys user_name].
Is remembering everything really that important?
We have to remember.
It's okay to forget.
But if Masaki's memories hadn't recovered...
Wouldn't they still be happy...?
Do we really have to remember everything? Even the bad things in our life?
If we do...
Isn't that kinda painful...?
I... Think so too.
If we can't ever forget any of the bad things in our life,
I think we'd break down.
The act of saving someone...
Does it have to go beyond
saving them from attacking demons...?
Saving someone... What does that even mean...?
>Jabo is sitting atop the tallest part of the surrounding ruins.
>Oblivious to him watching you, you are just about to leave the city.
So you've found the truth behind this city.
Which path do you think they'll choose now?
Will they accept their past and return to their original selves...?
Or will they overwrite the memory of even this incident and become someone new...?
